# Vendored from https://github.com/eyereasoner/eye/blob/master/reasoning/peano/peano.n3
# Unmodified.
#
# BLOCKED (see manifest.json "status": "ignored"): Peano arithmetic here is
# encoded entirely as nested nullary/backward rules over nested list terms,
# e.g. `{(?A 0) :add ?A} <= true.` and `{(?A (:s ?B)) :add (:s ?C)} <= {(?A ?B)
# :add ?C.}`, requiring genuine structural unification of nested list-term
# patterns against nested list-term facts/derived values (matching `:s`
# wrapped depths against a variable), recursively, driven backward from a
# query goal. As documented in good_cobbler.n3 above, this engine has no
# list-pattern structural unification at all (only opaque-id equality) and
# no backward/goal-directed evaluation -- both of which peano fundamentally
# requires, compounded by recursive nesting. Completely out of scope.
@prefix log: <http://www.w3.org/2000/10/swap/log#>.
@prefix : <http://example.org/#>.

{(?A 0) :add ?A} <= true.

{(?A (:s ?B)) :add (:s ?C)} <= {
    (?A ?B) :add ?C.
}.

{(?A 0) :multiply 0} <= true.

{(?A (:s ?B)) :multiply ?C} <= {
    (?A ?B) :multiply ?D.
    (?A ?D) :add ?C.
}.

{?A :factorial ?B} <= {
    (?A (:s 0)) :fac ?B.
}.

{(0 ?A) :fac ?A} <= true.

{((:s ?A) ?B) :fac ?C} <= {
    (?B (:s ?A)) :multiply ?D.
    (?A ?D) :fac ?C.
}.
